oc=NA"}],"languagesHumanTranslated":[],"languagesMachineTranslated":[],"caseNumber":"000073557","ipRight":"EUTM","outcome":"EUTM cancelled","appealed":"No","entityNumber":"019082313","entityStatus":"Registration cancellation pending","norms":["Article 59(1)(b) EUTMR"],"entityName":"Pallet Mole Jr","entityType":"Word","cancelledClasses":["7"],"earlierName":"PALLET MOLE","earlierType":"Word"},{"type":"APPEAL","typeLabel":"Appeal","date":"20/03/2026","uniqueSolrKey":"APL_20260320_R1202_2025-5_018481066","url":"https://euipo.europa.eu/eSearchCLW/#key/trademark/APL_20260320_R1202_2025-5_018481066","languagesOriginal":[{"code":"en","label":"English","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018481066/download/CLW/APL/2026/EN/20260320_R1202_2025-5.pdf?app=caselaw&casenum=R1202/2025-5&trTypeDoc=NA"}],"languagesHumanTranslated":[],"languagesMachineTranslated":[{"code":"es","label":"español (es)","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018481066/download/CLW/APL/2026/ES/20260320_R1202_2025-5.pdf?app=caselaw&casenum=R1202/2025-5&trTypeDoc=eTranslation&sourceLang=en","serviceProvider":"eTranslation"},{"code":"de","label":"Deutsch (de)","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018481066/download/CLW/APL/2026/DE/20260320_R1202_2025-5.pdf?app=caselaw&casenum=R1202/2025-5&trTypeDoc=eTranslation&sourceLang=en","serviceProvider":"eTranslation"},{"code":"fr","label":"français (fr)","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018481066/download/CLW/APL/2026/FR/20260320_R1202_2025-5.pdf?app=caselaw&casenum=R1202/2025-5&trTypeDoc=eTranslation&sourceLang=en","serviceProvider":"eTranslation"},{"code":"it","label":"italiano (it)","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018481066/download/CLW/APL/2026/IT/20260320_R1202_2025-5.pdf?app=caselaw&casenum=R1202/2025-5&trTypeDoc=eTranslation&sourceLang=en","serviceProvider":"eTranslation"}],"quotation":"(20/03/2026, R 1202/2025‑5, virtue)","documentKind":"Decision","caseNumber":"R1202/2025-5","ipRight":"EUTM","outcome":"Decision confirmed","appealed":"No","entityNumber":"018481066","entityStatus":"Registration cancellation pending","norms":["Article 59(1)(b) EUTMR"],"relatedCases":[{"id":"CCL_20250512_000064992_018481066","label":"Cancellation decision 000064992","url":"https://euipo.europa.eu/eSearchCLW/#key/trademark/CCL_20250512_000064992_018481066"}],"entityName":"virtue","entityType":"Word","nickName":"virtue","keywords":["Bad faith","Copyright","Filing date"],"summary":"Nothing in the file, however, shows any presence of a dishonest intention of the EUTM proprietor at the time of filing. On the contrary, it would rather seem that the business relationship between the parties ended sourly and that the cancellation applicant, when the cooperation resulted in an unpleasant ‘divorce’, intends to claim the right on the contested EUTM, alleging that the EUTM proprietor acted in bad faith when filing it. The filing of the EUTM in the name of the EUTM proprietor appears to have been made in the pursuit of a common legitimate goal rather than as an act of misappropriating someone else’s designation. As regards the existence of the alleged copyright on the name ‘Virtue’, copyright does not typically protect single words or short phrases because these are considered too minimal to meet the threshold of originality required for copyright protection and that words themselves, when used as trade marks, are not subject to copyright protection. The existence of any possible copyright (which will become clear does not exist) is in any event irrelevant for the purpose of this case.Mr S and the cancellation applicant decided to enter into an employment and service agreement with the EUTM proprietor, clearly knowing that all intellectual property rights of the project related to ‘Virtue’ would be owned by Snautic / Virtue Yachts. The contested EUTM was filed in the context of the cooperation with Mr S and the cancellation applicant on the ‘Virtue’ project, who actively were part of it through employment and service agreements, but who appear to be unsatisfied with the termination of the cooperation and with the fact that the intellectual property rights of the project remained with the EUTM proprietor.","entityClasses":["12 28 40"],"earlierName":"(Trade mark without text)","entityResult":"Trade mark remains valid","deemedDeliveredToAppellantDate":"30/03/2026","deemedDeliveredToDefendantDate":"28/03/2026"},{"type":"CANCELLATION","typeLabel":"Cancellation decision","date":"19/03/2026","uniqueSolrKey":"CCL_20260319_000071579_018900705","url":"https://euipo.europa.eu/eSearchCLW/#key/trademark/CCL_20260319_000071579_018900705","languagesOriginal":[{"code":"en","label":"English","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018900705/download/CLW/CCL/2026/EN/20260319_000071579.doc?app=caselaw&casenum=000071579&trTypeDoc=NA"}],"languagesHumanTranslated":[],"languagesMachineTranslated":[{"code":"es","label":"español (es)","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018900705/download/CLW/CCL/2026/ES/20260319_000071579.doc?app=caselaw&casenum=000071579&trTypeDoc=eTranslation&sourceLang=en","serviceProvider":"eTranslation"},{"code":"fr","label":"français (fr)","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018900705/download/CLW/CCL/2026/FR/20260319_000071579.doc?app=caselaw&casenum=000071579&trTypeDoc=eTranslation&sourceLang=en","serviceProvider":"eTranslation"},{"code":"it","label":"italiano (it)","pdfUrl":"https://euipo.europa.eu/copla/trademark/data/018900705/download/CLW/CCL/2026/IT/20260319_000071579.doc?app=caselaw&casenum=000071579&trTypeDoc=eTranslation&sourceLang=en","serviceProvider":"eTranslation"}],"caseNumber":"000071579","ipRight":"EUTM","outcome":"Cancellation rejected","appealed":"No","entityNumber":"018900705","entityStatus":"Registration cancellation pending","norms":["Article 59(1)(b) EUTMR","Article 60(1)(a) EUTMR","Article 8(1)(b) EUTMR"],"entityImage":"/copla/image/CJ4JX4FZVCC